{"TopicId":218737,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"Camera speed affected by approaching each pole","CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-02T13:00:15Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-02T13:00:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.3.2 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-10700 CPU @ 2.90GHz | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0NVIDIA GeForce RTX 2070 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObserved:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe camera speed is affected by which pole (north/south) you\u0027re looking at:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the Tracking Station or in the Map View The closer to the North pole you are, the more the camera speed is high and vice versa when you move close to the South pole, the camera speed get closer to 0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExpected:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn ksp1 the movement speed was unaffected by the position. (See the videos)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ECamera movements in ksp2:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cvideo class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 controls=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.global.core.embeddedvideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Csource type=\u0022video/mp4\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_12/camera_movement_ksp2.mp4.38d40256cd51ee422b1c7e90d1d543ca.mp4\u0022\u003E\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/attachment.php?id=1239\u0026amp;key=da16bc6ce0442ef28d7472cfde9dc546\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221239\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022mp4\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ecamera_movement_ksp2.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/video\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCamera movements in ksp1:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cvideo class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 controls=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.global.core.embeddedvideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Csource type=\u0022video/mp4\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2023_12/camera_movement_ksp1.mp4.933a7cbbe64747a2504c4c7b434c6230.mp4\u0022\u003E\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/attachment.php?id=1240\u0026amp;key=decb398afb9332072266be2fe548d987\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221240\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022mp4\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ecamera_movement_ksp1.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/video\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-27T14:03:24Z\u0022 title=\u002212/27/2023 02:03  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 27\u0022\u003EDecember 27, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Spicat\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-03T04:20:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso applies to looking at a craft in map view, it\u0027s not just planets.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-02T20:39:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill the case for 0.1.4.0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere a video with the craft this time to show what Anth is saying:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/ZalBE63\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/a/ZalBE63\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-28T19:54:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.5 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 5 7600X | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Nvidia RTX 4070 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32 GB DDR5\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn map view, panning the camera is fast when looking at CB north pole (from above) and slow when looking at CB south pole (from below).\u003Cbr\u003E\nThere might be an older bug report related to this - it\u0027s an ancient issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-28T21:10:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/228085-spicat/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022228085\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profi